<b>Yep indeed - </b>6/23/02 9:08:55 PM<br>~ <b>Tahmay</b><blockquote>I was gonna say what Steppy said about locating corpses with this song.  It's simply the best way to find the corpse for that ever-present &quot;I have no idea where I died at&quot; n00b who wants your help finding a corpse.<br><br>I personally use this to check pops in a camp, like if I'm doing raptors I just stay where I can see one of them and then bind sight to it so I will know exactly when the others pop and exactly when the one roamer is clear so I can go charm away =)<br> <br>I'd rate this song higher but it's a utility song not something you kill with.<br><br>Agreed that it's great to help a group member navigate a zone.  Just look at what they see and talk them through how to get to your location.  Simple and wonderful.<br><br></blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
<b>Best Uses for this song - </b>1/16/02 1:24:44 PM<br>~ <b>Steppy</b><blockquote>This song is great for locating lost corpses.  Target the person whose corpse is missing and sing Locating Lyric (lvl 4 song).  That puts their corpse in the target window.  Now, sing Solidarity of Vision and switch to an overhead view and you know exactly where the corpse is.  It is also great to stick on your puller in a dangerous zone -- he looks at a mob he can see through a doorway or down a hall, you switch vision to the mob, you can see the hidden ones around the corner.  Not an everyday song, but extremely useful at times.</blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
<b>Still lovin this song - </b>1/4/02 12:17:07 PM<br>~ <b>Kocho Divah</b><blockquote>I wish they would give me an item that has this triggered effect! I find myself using it every day.<br><br>Here's my favorite uses:<br><br>1) To scout out new zones - Go invis, run out in a new zone, target a mob. Run back to safety, then bind sight from the mob to the next mob until you've seen the whole zone. I've done this in Umbral Plains and Akheva and Maidens very easily. If you don't want to run out, bind sight to the puller and do the same.<br><br>2) Use on the puller - to see what mobs and how many are being pulled back. If more than one, step out a bit from group to stop the adds in their tracks before they reach the group, using mezz song. You can also know beforehand what mob is best to attack first and which to mezz/charm.<br><br>3) Locate corpse - If someone died and lost their body, group with them, and have them in the zone. Then Lyssa's Locate their corpse, and Bind Sight to it. Use different views to see where the corpse is.<br><br>4) See the Uber mob safely! - Get your screenshots in the safety of the raid group simply by binding sight to the main puller, and hopping around on targets until you've reached your uber mob.<br><br>5)Guide someone in your group to a spot - You can look through their eyes and help them through the zone<br><br>6) Spy on your boyfriend - Suspect your hubby/boyfriend is checking out all the dark elves? Bind sight to him, and see what females he's looking at!</blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
<b>Excellent for Rallos - </b>1/2/02 7:57:29 PM<br>~ <b>Tom Strife</b><blockquote>I play on Rallos Zek and when i fight people (especially other wizards or necros who use Shadow Step) this song is very useful (especially when they are low on life and are currently meditating)</blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
<b>Peeping Tom - </b>3/22/01 2:41:38 AM<br>~ <b>Kocho Divah</b><blockquote>I feel like such a peeping tom using this song. Apparently, the person doesn't know you're looking through their eyes. You can have alot of fun with it, I start it up in a new zone, look through the puller's eyes to get used to the zone, bounce from mob to mob to corpse to person to mob, etc...<br><br>I find it deliciously fun on dragon raids. While sitting around being bored while getting buffed, I target the monk that is pulling, then bounce from her eyes, eventually to the dragons, so I can keep the group/guild updated on what's happening! Last I did this, I could simply type in the puller's name /assist puller_name and I automatically targeted their target, even if I couldn't see them. I suspect this has been fixed though, I'll keep you updated...</blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
